rComments: not sure what some of these other comments are about... difficult lectures, lots of notes, but exams are written to be completed easily if you actually studied/attended class/paid minimal attention. her study sessions are a great help. she will take any comments/suggestions you make into consideration, especially about the exams.

she gets a bad rap, but i'm not sure why. if you don't like her lectures, don't go, the notes she reads from are online, as well as the powerpoint slides she uses. her exams are a bit strenuous, time-wise, but the material is not complicated. her take on the material she presents is usually very original and impressive.

Trish is not the devil that some people make her out to be. Her tests are not all that difficult if you actually take the time to study for them. What nobody here has mentioned yet is that if you failed the midterm, you had the chance to drop the grade completely in place of the grade you got on the final exam. Her lectures are very bland though.

I think she may have read some of the comments previously posted on the website and completely changed when I had her.  We lucked out sort of and had a small class so it was easier to pay attention and learn.  You HAD to go to class and read.  She held test reviews and brought donuts & pizza.  3 or 4 small tests and gives study guides!  Pretty easy

Good: she offered a large selection of paper topics.
 Bad: the grading was strict, the tests were long and difficult, the lectures were extremely boring, and she was very rude. She told the class that she intentionally made the midterm difficult in order to punish those who did not come to lecture and those who slept through it.. ?! not very fair.
There are exactly 5 reasons why this story works. Exactly 3 reasons why that other one doesn't. Exactly 2 interpretations of it all. Memorize it. Also, be bland. Be very bland.
Trish is crazy, her tests were literally impossible to finish, as evident in the amount of F's she enjoyed handing out.

Lectures are boring...She doesn't use a mic a lot of the time, and I never want to see another timeline again after taking this class.  Exams are HARD and take more time than you're given.  If you have to take this class, get a really good TA and read all texts and study HARD.  Seriously.

Joyless and very condescending towards the class. Her tests were easy but she gave us very little time to do them. When OVER HALF the class received D's or F's on the midterm exam, her response was that we should "get serious". Also employs a nigh-exclusively autobiographical interpretation for nearly every text we read. Not fun or good at all.
borrrrrrring lecture, tests were very hard. TONS of reading
